   The U.S. Department of Justice launched a new Victims and Family
       Assistance  Web site to deliver crucial and timely information to
       those who need it most - terrorism victims and their families. This
       new victims-only Web site will include information about emergency
       assistance, legal rights and services, updates on the criminal
       justice response, and resources for coping with the emotional
       trauma.
