     STATUTES
   Under California law (Government Code Sections 13959 - 13969.5 and
   13970 - 13974.1), certain victims of crime may receive payments from
   the Restitution Fund for unreimbursed losses directly resulting from a
   crime. The Restitution Fund is the VOC Program's primary funding source
   and it receives monies collected through fines and penalties imposed by
   judges upon persons convicted of crimes and traffic offenses in
   California.

